description: Shared lib code — types, pure logic, and HTTP helpers
globs: src/lib/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Library modules (`src/lib`)

- **Purity**: Keep penalty/business logic (e.g. `src/lib/penalty/`) testable and side-effect free where possible.
- **Types**: Prefer explicit types; avoid `any`. Use Zod-inferred types from validators when sharing shapes with API routes.
- **Errors**: Use `HttpError` from `@/lib/http` for API-layer failures with status codes; do not catch and swallow errors without handling.
- **Duplicates**: Extend existing helpers (`warehouse-access`, `query-scope`, `validators`) instead of reimplementing access rules.
